ntile.R** (Full file read)\n**Key Test Patterns**:\n- Uses `example_quantile` dataset extensively (lines 6, 207-214, 422)\n- Test structure: `test_that(\"description\", { ... })`\n- Common patterns:\n  - `expect_s3_class()` for class checking\n  - `expect_no_condition()` for passing cases\n  - `expect_error()` / `expect_warning()` for failing cases\n  - `expect_identical()` for exact comparisons\n  - `suppressMessages(suppressWarnings())` wrapper around `as_forecast_quantile()` calls\n  \n**Examples**:\n```r\ntest_that(\"as_forecast_quantile() works as expected\", {\n  test <- na.omit(data.table::copy(example_quantile))\n  expect_s3_class(\n    as_forecast_quantile(test),\n    c(\"forecast_quantile\", \"forecast\", \"data.table\", \"data.frame\"),\n    exact = TRUE\n  )\n})\n```\n\n#### **tests/testthat/test-metrics-quantile.R** (Lines 707-876)\n**Monotonicity-Related Tests** (existing tests for bias_quantile):\n- Line 837-850: `test_that(\"bias_quantile(): quantiles must be increasing\", {...})`\n  - Tests that non-monotonic predictions **error** with message: `\"Predictions must not be decreasing with increasing quantile level\"`\n  - Example: `predicted <- c(1, 2, 4, 3)` with `quantiles <- c(0.1, 0.3, 0.5, 0.9)` triggers error\n  \n- Line 852-861: `test_that(\"bias_quantile(): predictions must be increasing\", {...})`\n  - Tests strictly decreasing predictions\n  - Uses `expect_error()` to verify error is raised\n\n**Key Code Snippets**:\n```r\ntest_that(\"bias_quantile(): predictions must be increasing\", {\n  predicted <- c(1, 2, 4, 3)\n  quantiles <- c(0.1, 0.3, 0.5, 0.9)\n  expect_error(\n    bias_quantile(observed = 3, predicted, quantiles),\n    \"Predictions must not be decreasing with increasing quantile level\"\n  )\n  expect_silent(bias_quantile(observed = 3, 1:4, quantiles))\n})\n```\n\n#### **tests/testthat/setup.R** (Lines 1-26)\n**Test Fixtures**:\n```r\ndata.table::setDTthreads(2) # restricts number of cores used on CRAN\n\nmetrics_no_cov <- get_me