spects verbose flag):\n  if (!isTRUE(number_quantiles_samples) && verbose) {\n    cli_warn(number_quantiles_samples)\n  }\n  \n  return(data[])\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### **6. DUAL-FUNCTION PATTERN FROM get_duplicate_forecasts()**\n\nFile: `/Users/nikos/github-synced/scoringutils-pipeline/R/get-duplicate-forecasts.R`\n\n**User-facing function** (`get_duplicate_forecasts()`):\n```r\nget_duplicate_forecasts <- function(\n  data,\n  forecast_unit = NULL,\n  counts = FALSE\n) {\n  assert_data_frame(data)\n  data <- ensure_data.table(data)\n\n  if (!is.null(forecast_unit)) {\n    data <- set_forecast_unit(data, forecast_unit)\n  }\n  forecast_unit <- get_forecast_unit(data)\n  available_type <- c(\"sample_id\", \"quantile_level\", \"predicted_label\") %in% colnames(data)\n  type <- c(\"sample_id\", \"quantile_level\", \"predicted_label\")[available_type]\n  data <- as.data.table(data)\n  data[, scoringutils_InternalDuplicateCheck := .N, by = c(forecast_unit, type)]\n  out <- data[scoringutils_InternalDuplicateCheck > 1]\n\n  col <- colnames(data)[\n    colnames(data) %in% c(\"sample_id\", \"quantile_level\", \"predicted_label\")\n  ]\n  setorderv(out, cols = c(forecast_unit, col, \"predicted\"))\n  out[, scoringutils_InternalDuplicateCheck := NULL]\n\n  if (counts) {\n    out <- out[, .(n_duplicates = .N), by = c(get_forecast_unit(out))]\n  }\n\n  return(out[])\n}\n```\n\n**Internal check function** (`check_duplicates()`):\n```r\ncheck_duplicates <- function(data) {\n  check_duplicates <- get_duplicate_forecasts(data)\n  if (nrow(check_duplicates) > 0) {\n    msg <- paste0(\n      \"There are instances with more than one forecast for the same target. \",\n      \"This can't be right and needs to be resolved. Maybe you need to \",\n      \"check the unit of a single forecast and add missing columns? Use \",\n      \"the function get_duplicate_forecasts() to identify duplicate rows\"\n    )\n    return(msg)\n  }\n  return(TRUE)\n}\n```\n\n**Usage in assert function**:\n```r\n# From class-forecast.R line 128\nassert(check_duplicates(data))\n```\n\n---\n\n### **7. RELATED ISSUE DOCUMENTATION**\n\nFile: `/Users/nikos/github-synced/scoringutils-pipeline/.ralph/issues/895-quantile-prediction-order.md`\n\n**Key Requirements**:\n1. Create `get_non_monotonic_forecasts()` — user-facing diagnostic function\n2. Add warning in `assert_forecast.forecast_quantile()` when non-monotonic forecasts detected\n3. Create internal helper `check_monotonicity()` following the pattern of `check_duplicates()`\n\n**Test Specifications** (12 test cases defined):\n1. Returns empty data.table for well-formed quantile forecasts\n2. Detects predictions that decrease with increasing quantile level\n3. Handles multiple forecast units with mixed monotonicity\n4. Works with `counts` argument\n5. Accepts custom `forecast_unit` argument\n6. Returns expected class (data.table)\n7. Works with plain data.frame input\n8. `assert_forecast.forecast_quantile()` warns about non-monotonic predictions\n9. Does not warn for well-formed data\n10. Suppresses warning when `verbose = FALSE`\n11. `score()` works end-to-end excluding bias metrics\n12. Handles equal predictions at adjacent quantile levels (flat segments OK)\n\n---\n\n### **8. KEY CODE PATTERNS TO FOLLOW**\n\n#### **Data Table Operations**:\n```r\n# Grouping and ordering\ndata[, new_col := .N, by = forecast_unit]\nsetorderv(data, cols = c(forecast_unit, \"quantile_level\", \"predicted\"))\n\n# Filtering\nresult <- data[scoringutils_InternalCheck > 0]\n\n# Summary aggregation\nresult <- result[, .(count = .N), by = forecast_unit]\n```\n\n#### **CLI Messages**:\n```r\n# Import\nimportFrom cli cli_warn cli_abort cli_inform\n\n# Usage\ncli_warn(c(\n  \"!\" = \"Warning message with {.val variable} formatting\"\n))\n\ncli_abort(c(\n  \"!\" = \"Error message with {.val variable} formatting\"\n))\n\ncli_inform(c(\n  \"i\" = \"Informational message\"\n))\n```\n\n#### **Returning Data**:\n```r\n# Always return with [] to force printing/stripping class temporarily\nreturn(data[])\n```\n\n---\n\n### **9. QUANTILE LEVEL ORDERING AND PREDICTIONS**\n\nFrom the existing `bias_quantile_single_vector()` check (line 493-504):\n\n```r\norder <- order(quantile_level)\npredicted <- predicted[order]  # REORDER by quantile_level\nif (!all(diff(predicted) >= 0)) {\n  # Violation: predicted is DECREASING somewhere\n  cli_abort(\"Predictions must not be decreasing with increasing quantile level.\")\n}\n```\n\n**Critical Implementation Detail**: \n- Within a forecast unit, predictions must be sorted by `quantile_level`\n- Then check `diff(predicted) >= 0` (all differences must be non-negative)\n- Allows equality (flat segments), only rejects strictly decreasing values\n\n---\n\n### **10. ABSOLUTE FILE PATHS FOR REFERENCE**\n\n| Component | File Path |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| Main quantile class | `/Users/nikos/github-synced/scoringutils-pipeline/R/class-forecast-quantile.R` |\n| Quantile metrics | `/Users/nikos/github-synced/scoringutils-pipeline/R/metrics-quantile.R` |\n| Duplicate forecasts helper (model) | `/Users/nikos/github-synced/scoringutils-pipeline/R/get-duplicate-forecasts.R` |\n| Check input helpers | `/Users/nikos/github-synced/scoringutils-pipeline/R/check-input-helpers.R` |\n| Main forecast class | `/Users/nikos/github-synced/scoringutils-pipeline/R/class-forecast.R` |\n| Quantile class tests | `/Users/nikos/github-synced/scoringutils-pipeline/tests/testthat/test-class-forecast-quantile.R` |\n| Quantile metrics tests | `/Users/nikos/github-synced/scoringutils-pipeline/tests/testthat/test-metrics-quantile.R` |\n| Duplicate forecasts tests | `/Users/nikos/github-synced/scoringutils-pipeline/tests/testthat/test-get-duplicate-forecasts.R` |\n| Test setup/fixtures | `/Users/nikos/github-synced/scoringutils-pipeline/tests/testthat/setup.R` |\n| Example data creation | `/Users/nikos/github-synced/scoringutils-pipeline/inst/create-example-data.R` |\n| Issue 895 spec | `/Users/nikos/github-synced/scoring